{
  "_doc": "Phase-3e demo: width-changers and the display sink. Three independent paths in one scene:\n  • SIGN_EXT 4→8: sign-extends a 4-bit input to 8 bits via the canonical Verilog `{{4{in[3]}}, in}` replicate-concat.\n  • BUS_MUX 2:1 (8-bit): selects between two 8-bit buses with a clean ternary `(s ? b : a)`.\n  • DISPLAY_7SEG: seven 1-bit inputs (a..g) become a 7-bit output port `seg7[6:0]`, packed via Verilog concat `{g, f, e, d, c, b, a}`.\nClick VERILOG to see all three lower in the same module.",
  "nodes": [
